Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the 75th Convention of the National Religious Broadcasters in Nashville, Tennessee. He thanked the organization for their support and highlighted the achievements of the Trump administration, including tax cuts, job creation, and the appointment of conservative judges. Pence also emphasized the administration's commitment to protecting religious freedom and the sanctity of life. He spoke about the importance of faith and community in addressing the challenges facing the nation, and called on the NRB to continue spreading their message of hope and renewal. Pence also addressed the recent school shooting in Parkland, Florida, promising that the administration would take action to make schools safer. He concluded his speech by urging the NRB to pray for America and have faith in the country's future.